            <title><![CDATA[Cotton Reboot! High Tension! delayed to July 31 in Japan]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/06/cotton-reboot-high-tension-delayed-to-july-31-in-japan</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/cotton-reboot-high-tension-delayed-to-july-31-in-japan.1227669/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps4">PS4</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PS5</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>A one-week delay.</span>
      </p></div><div><p><a title="Companies > Beep Japan [7 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/beep-japan">BEEP</a> has <a href="https://twitter.com/BEEP_SOFT/status/1937373779535311091" target="_blank">delayed</a> shoot ’em up sequel <em><a title="Games > Cotton Reboot! High Tension! [3 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/cotton-reboot-high-tension">Cotton Reboot! High Tension!</a></em> from its <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/01/cotton-reboot-high-tension-launches-july-24-in-japan">previously planned</a> July 24 release date to July 31 in Japan. It will be available for <a title="Platforms > PS5 [9,807 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PlayStation 5</a>, <a title="Platforms > PS4 [28,121 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps4">PlayStation 4</a>, and <a title="Platforms > Switch [17,271 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a>. <span id="more-975906"></span></p><p>Here is a overview of the game, via our <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/01/cotton-reboot-high-tension-debut-trailer-details-and-screenshots">previous coverage</a>:</p><blockquote><p>A sequel to the 2021-released <em><a title="Games > Cotton Reboot! [16 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/cotton-reboot">Cotton Reboot!</a></em> The gluttonous witch Nata de <a title="Series > Cotton [12 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/series/cotton">Cotton</a> is back in <a title="Genres > Action [2,833 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/action">action</a>! Dig into this powered-up, exhilarating witch <a title="Genres > Shoot 'Em Up [797 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/shoot-em-up">shoot ’em up game</a>!</p><p>This sequel to the <a title="Genres > Side-Scrolling [1,029 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/side-scrolling">side-scrolling</a> shoot ’em up <em>Cotton Reboot!</em> has been meticulously crafted from the ground up.</p><p>While “Willows” are an important item in the <em>Cotton</em> series, this time they’ve taken on a sinister form, plunging the fairy kingdom into chaos. Joining Cotton and Silk on this absurd <a title="Genres > Adventure [2,373 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/adventure">adventure</a> is the new character Macaron.</p><p>The gameplay is even more thrilling, with beautiful graphics and powerful new magic. Additionally, when you collect a certain number of items, you’ll enter “Over Tension,” unlocking a level of “high tension” never-before-seen in the series.</p><!-- AD: content -->
        <p>Along with returning classic magic like “Fire Dragon” and “Lightning,” the game introduces a new attack system called “Enemy Capture,” which lets you use enemy characters to help clear each stage. The “Fever” system from the previous game also returns, now enhanced as the more-exhilarating “Willow Fever.”</p><p>When your gauge reaches 100 percent, “Over Tension” will activate, doubling your score. Enemy attacks become more extreme, but you can use powerful hidden magic to significantly boost your score. Aim for the high score!</p><p>Former Namco composer Hiroyuki Kawada (known for works like <em>Valkyrie no Bouken</em> and <em>Youkai Douchuki</em>) and chiptune music unit YMCK are composing the stage music. The game will be further elevated with new tracks by this exceptional composition team.</p><p>The voice cast was chosen from over 200 applicants who auditioned.</p></blockquote></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/06/cotton-reboot-high-tension-delayed-to-july-31-in-japan]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
